# Description
A row of 2n seats with n couples is given where each couple is numbered consecutively like (0,1), (2,3), and so on. 
The seating order is stored in an array, and the goal is to find the minimum number of swaps needed so that each couple sits next to each other. A swap can be made between any two people. 
The algorithm checks the seats in pairs and swaps people when a couple is not sitting together, keeping track of positions to do this efficiently in linear time.

